-- Barclays Said to Consider Sale of Credit-Card Backed Bonds
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-02-10T14:01:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-10/barclays-said-to-consider-sale-of-credit-card-backed-bonds.html
Barclays Bank Plc plans to meet with
investors in  Europe  and the U.S. that may lead to an issue of
bonds backed by credit cards, according to three people with
knowledge of the matter.  Barclays Capital and JPMorgan Chase & Co. are organizing
the meetings, which start Feb. 15, the people said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
 eduarterubia@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
